FBIS4-63458 "drsov099_e_94005" FBIS-SOV-94-099 Daily Report 23 May 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Fleet Exercises End; 50,000 Troops Said in Crimea Fleet Exercises End; 50,000 Troops Said in Crimea LD2305081394 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0730 GMT 23 May 94 LD2305081394 Moscow 2x2 Television Russian BFN [Excerpts] The largest Black Sea Fleet exercises for some time have ended in the Crimea. Approximately 30 ships, coastal units, and aviation took part. Subunits and ships are now in their usual places of deployment and there are no troop movements. The maneuvers demonstrated the fleet's high degree of combat readiness. [passage omitted] On the whole the situation remains calm throughout the peninsula, but according to the latest figures there are now approximately 50,000 Ukrainian soldiers in Crimea, and their number continues to increase. Mainly they are special purpose units.
